Author:
Vol / Page: 2/400
Edition: 1960
Quote: ... I get quite enough of lessons in school [Nelson College] so I will go on to our gallant cadet corps. ... the [uniform] jumper or loose jacket is more grand, the cuffs of the sleaves [sic] have a red twirligig of braid on them ... [ed. fn. The cadet corps was formed in 1875. the first captain was Joseph Mackay, who was resident master at the [Nelson] College (1865-81) ...]
Notes: (?Bill Atkinson, Nelson, 15 years)

